Wazuh on EC2
    EC2 Setup:
      Name: Wazuh
      OS: ubuntu/images/hvm-ssd/ubuntu-jammy-22.04-amd64-server-20240927
      Instance Type: c5.xlarge
      Storage: 50 GB

  Installation:
      SSH into the Ubuntu server on AWS.
      Run:
        bash  Copy code
            apt-get update && apt upgrade -y
      Download and install Wazuh:
        bash Copy code
            curl -sO https://packages.wazuh.com/4.7/wazuh-install.sh && sudo bash ./wazuh-install.sh -a
              Note the default Wazuh credentials:
              User: admin
              Password: <Password>

    Configuration:
      Extract configuration files:
        bash Copy code
          tar -xvf wazuh-install-files.tar
      Retrieve passwords:
        bash Copy code
          cat <path_to_files>/wazuh-install-files/wazuh-passwords.txt
      Admin user credentials:
          Username: admin
          Password: <password>
      API user credentials:
          Username: wazuh-wui
          Password: <Password>
      Access the Wazuh Dashboard:

Use the public IP of the Wazuh EC2 instance in a browser.
